<DOC><DOCNO> AP890503-0304 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-89 2114EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Ogilvy     05-03 0207</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Ogilvy,0215</SECOND><HEAD>Ogilvy First-Quarter Earnings Up 10.6 Percent</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ogilvy Group Inc., the advertising agencyholding company under threat of a hostile takeover, said Wednesdayits first-quarter profit rose 10.6 percent over the same 1988period.   Ogilvy reported net income of $3.8 million, or 26 cents a share,on revenue of $197.7 million. That compared with earnings of $3.43million, or 24 cents a share, on revenue of $191.1 million in thefirst quarter last year.   The New York company attributed the gains to strong overseasperformances. It said foreign advertising revenues increased 12.6percent while domestic advertising revenues were flat.   WPP Group PLC of London, which owns J. Walter Thompson, the bigNew York advertising firm, made an unsolicited $730 million bid forOgilvy last week. Ogilvy, parent company of Ogilvy andamp; MatherWorldwide, said it wants to remain independent.   Ogilvy, the world's fifth-largest ad holding company, saidquarterly advertising revenues increased 5 percent to $123.6million from $117.7 million a year ago. Its public relationsdivision, which includes Adams andamp; Rhinehart, showed a 30 percentrevenue rise, to $12.99 million.   Its marketing research division revenue declined 10 percent,while other areas suffered a 23 percent drop, principally fromdivested operations.</TEXT></DOC>